      • createFrom

        Optional<I> createFrom(DataHolder dataHolder)
        Attempts to read data from the given DataHolder and constructs a new copy of the DataManipulator as an instance of T.

        If the DataHolder does not contain the necessary information to pre-populate the DataManipulator, a fresh new DataManipulator is returned. If the DataManipulator is incompatible with the DataHolder, Optional.absent() is returned.

        Parameters:
        dataHolder - The DataHolder to extract data
        Returns:
        A new instance of this DataManipulator with relevant data filled from the given DataHolder, if available
